obo:GO_0003674  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_2523  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.6: \"LRRK2 associates with lipid rafts at synaptic membranes in mouse brain.\"\n- \"LRRK2 is considerably present in the synaptosomal fraction (P2') and cofractionated with NR1A and synaptophysin, indicating its localization in synaptic terminals, including synaptic plasma membranes (LP1) and synaptic vesicles (LP2). Intriguingly, we also identify LRRK2 signal in the soluble fraction of synaptic terminal (LS2) (Fig. 6A), again suggesting its weak association with the synaptic membranes.\"\n\nFig. 7. LRRK2 colocalize with synaptotagmin I in mouse striatal neurons.\n\nLiteral:\n\"We also analyzed subcellular localization of LRRK2 in mouse primary cultured neurons. In consistent with the data in Fig. 3D, LRRK2 colocalizes with synaptotagmin I in the processes of mouse striatal neurons, indicating its association with synaptic vesicles. In addition, we found perinuclear localization of LRRK2 costained with g-adaptin in mouse cortical neurons (Fig. 7).\"\n\nFig. 8C. Transfected human LRRK2 colocalize with synaptotagmin I in mouse cortical neurons.\n\nLiteral:\n\"Furthermore, we examined the effect of mutant using mouse primary cortical neurons transfected with FLAG-tagged WT and I2020T LRRK2. Confocal microscopic analyses reveal that both the WT and I2020T mutant LRRK2 colocalize with synaptotagmin I and PIP2 (Fig. 8C). These results indicate that mutations in LRRK2 alter neither its subcellular localization nor its association with lipid rafts.\". Experimental description: for immunostaining primary cortical and striatum neuronal cells from mice were used. Human LRRK2 cDNA for transfection was used.\n\nLiteral from M&M:\n\"Primary cortical and striatum neuronal cells containing glia cells were prepared from E15.5 C57B6J mice\"\n\"To generate LRRK2 mutant vectors, the QuikChange site-directed mutagenesis kit (Stratagene; La Jolla, CA) was used at provided condition. The amino acid sequence of each vector was compared with the current Entrez database entry for LRRK2 (accession No. AY792511).\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
